OL,6,FMr Pengelly continued: "The Executive
OL,7,Fhasn't been back for very long. I
OL,8,Fdon't doubt that in the coming weeks
OL,9,Fand months, the Executive will start
OL,10,Fto take a much more strategic grip of
OL,11,Fthe challenges they face and they
OL,12,Finevitably will start to think about
OL,13,Fsome medium and long-term solutions.
OL,15,F"In many ways, it's about survival in
OL,16,Fthe short term."
OL,18,FMr Pengelly described himself as the
OL,19,F"very new chief executive", pointing
OL,20,Fout that it was just halfway through
OL,21,Fhis second week in the job.
